It is considered as extremly rude and as a very problematic violation to reserve more than 2 weeks in advance, would it be for one day. (go to the rants forum, or even on the home-page if you want confirmation of this).<br>
It is also considered as offensive to reserve spots other than dragons, planes and some epic mobs. (if you want to do so anyway, really put a &quot;it's more an information than a real claim&quot; baseline under the reservation).<br>
Naggy spawns on tuesday, reserving it on saturday exposes you to the risk of seeing a guild reserving it on its spawn day, and thus letting you with an empty lair on saturday.<br>
I would recommend to be cautious with the Calendar to preserve Random Acts good reputation.<br>
<br>
As guids are growing in level and in number, more and more are capable of owning dragons or planes ; the reservation will thus be the basis of numerous conflicts to come. To help Morell-Thule keep being a friendly server, respecting the calendar rules is a crucial point that is not to be neglected in my honest opinion. <p><BR>
